+Name:           golang-github-spf13-cobra
+Version:        1.8.0
+Release:        0
+Summary:        Library for Creating CLI Applications in Go
+License:        Apache-2.0
+URL:            https://github.com/spf13/cobra
+Source0:        https://github.com/spf13/cobra/archive/refs/tags/v%{version}.tar.gz
+BuildRequires:  go-github-cpuguy83-go-md2man-v2 >= 2.0.3
+BuildRequires:  go-github-inconshreveable-mousetrap >= 1.1.0
+BuildRequires:  go-github-spf13-pflag >= 1.0.5
+BuildRequires:  go-gopkg-in-yaml.v3 >= 3.0.1
+BuildRequires:  golang
+BuildRequires:  golang-rpc
+
+%description
+Cobra is a library providing a simple interface for creating modern
+command line interfaces in Go. It offers fully POSIX-compliant flags,
+nested subcommands, intelligent suggestions, automatic help generation,
+shell autocompletion (bash, zsh, fish, powershell), and man page generation.
+
+Cobra is used by many popular Go projects including Kubernetes, Hugo,
+GitHub CLI, Docker, Homebrew, rkt, Helm, and others.
+
+%prep
+%autosetup -n cobra-%{version}
+# Remove vendored dependencies to use system packages instead
+rm -rf vendor
+
+%build
+# No compilation needed for pure Go library, deps are resolved at consumer build time
+
+%install
+goinstall -pkgname github.com/spf13/cobra \
+  -srcdir "%{SOURCE_DIR}" \
+  -prefix "/usr" %{?use_buildgo_opts}
+
+%files
+%{_golibdir}/github.com/spf13/cobra/
+
+%license LICENSE.txt
+
+%changelog
